===[[Etymology]]===

[From Dr. Laumont, the [[discoverer]].] ([[en:Laumont|Laumont]] + [[-ite]])
===[[Noun]]===

(Min.) A [[mineral]], of a white color and vitreous luster. It is a hydrous [[silicate]] of [[alumina]] and lime. Exposed to the air, it loses water, becomes [[opaque]], and crumbles. (Written also [[laumonite.]])
